title: Activation of 112Cd by deuteron induced reactions up to 50 MeV: An alternative for 111In production?

x4freetext: Activation of 112Cd by deuteron induced reactions up
to 50 MeV: An alternative for 111In production?

x4codes.hlp: Institute for Nuclear Research (ATOMKI), Debrecen, Hungary

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nucl. Instrum. Methods in Physics Res., Sect.B, Vol.339, p.26 (2014)

x4codes.hlp: Catholic Univ. of Louvain, Louvain-la-Neuve, Belgium

x4freetext: Highly enriched 112Cd electroplated on Cu backing.
Nominal thickness of the 112Cd layer was 14.67 mg/cm2
equivalent 16.96 um.
One stack
consisting of twenty two 112Cd on Cu-backing targets
interleaved with Al (151 and 102 um)
monitor/degraders, was irradiated with a 50 MeV
deuteron beam of the CGR930 cyclotron in Louvain la
Neuve (LLN). Irradiation was done in a Faraday-cup
type target holder with deuteron beam of 50nA for 1
hour. Beam intensity was monitored by using monitor
reactions. Activity was measured with no chemical
separation. Several series of spectra were recorded to
be able to follow the decay. Decay data were taken
from NUDAT online data library.

x4codes.shortRef: Rept: Nuclear Data Services (Doc. series of NDS), No.1211 (2001)

x4freetext: , Al+d
The uncertainty on the median energy in the
foils includes the cumulative effects of uncertainty of
incident beam energy, uncertainty of stopping power of
each foil due to thickness variation and  straggling
effects. Uncertainty of the primary incident beam was
+- 0.2MeV which increased up to +-1.8MeV in the last
foil of the stack.
The uncertainty on the cross section values
are estimated in the  standard way as the square root
of the quadratic summation of the independently
contributing parameters. Uncertainty of time parameters
is not included. Overall uncertainty were 10-13%.
surface density of target nuclei(5%),
incident charged particle flux (7%),
nuclear decay and branching data(2%)
detector efficiency (5%)
statistical and peak fitting (2-8%)
The experimental data were compared to the
results of the theoretical model codes TENDL-2013.
The measured experimental data were compared to
those found in the literature.
Fitted excitation functions were used for
determination of integral physical yields.
Entry was checked by the corresponding author.
